These give a usable Phase-1 platform that demonstrates value without complex finance logic.

Important business rules & validations (callouts)

Project cannot go live until title, category, stage, description, location, timeline, funding_required, at least one DPR/approval doc, and admin validation are present. Enforce this server-side. 

BA_Field_Catalogue

Funding gap must always be computed = funding_required − funds_secured (update on commits). 

BA_Field_Catalogue

Commitment must be positive amount. Updating commitments must instantly affect funding gap. 

BA_Field_Catalogue

DataRoom visibility: Phase-1 open; later phases may require NDA gating / restricted access. Build access grants from day 1 (simple “open” + manual grant).

Risks & suggested mitigations (practical)

Low document quality / missing DPRs → buyers lose trust.
Mitigation: strict admin validation checklist + file validation (hash, required types) + UI hints for missing items. 

BA_Field_Catalogue

Settlement happens off-platform (manual). This creates operational friction and trust gaps.
Mitigation: require settlement proof uploads and a simple escrow/trustee reference field; show settlement status prominently on listing. 

Marketplace_Vision

Access control mistakes → leaks of sensitive data.
Mitigation: implement AccessGrant model (view/download + expiry + via: open/club/bilateral). Log every download with watermarking. 

BA_Field_Catalogue

Complexity explosion when adding bidding/eligibility/ptc tranches later.
Mitigation: design models to be future-ready (keep fields but hide in UI). Use feature flags for Phase-2/3. 

Marketplace_Spec_Feedback_Updat…

Poor tape data quality for DA pools (Phase-2).
Mitigation: ingest validation reports, show stratification snapshots, and provide a “data quality” score to buyers. 

Marketplace_Spec_Feedback_Updat…

Implementation suggestions (practical tech + APIs)

You (as a Java/Spring dev) can follow a pragmatic stack:

Backend: Java Spring Boot (REST + Spring Security) — you already work with Spring.

DB: Postgres (jsonb for flexible fields like key_metrics, economics, eligibility rules).

File storage: S3 (or equivalent) for DataRoom; store file hash, version, watermark flag.

Auth & KYC: Keycloak or Spring Security + JWT; tie users to Parties.

Search & filters: ElasticSearch (optional later) for listings.

Cache: Redis for funding_gap and notifications.

Minimal REST endpoints (examples):

POST /api/parties — register seller/buyer. 

BA_Field_Catalogue

POST /api/listings — create project listing. 

BA_Field_Catalogue

GET /api/listings — list with filters (type, category, funding_gap). 

